{"task_id": "count-triplets-with-even-xor-set-bits-ii", "question_id": 3215, "difficulty": "Medium", "tags": ["Bit Manipulation", "Array"], "problem_description": "Given three integer arrays a, b, and c, return the number of triplets (a[i], b[j], c[k]), such that the bitwise XOR between the elements of each triplet has an even number of set bits.\n \nExample 1:\n\nInput: a = [1], b = [2], c = [3]\nOutput: 1\nExplanation:\nThe only triplet is (a[0], b[0], c[0]) and their XOR is: 1 XOR 2 XOR 3 = 002.\n\nExample 2:\n\nInput: a = [1,1], b = [2,3], c = [1,5]\nOutput: 4\nExplanation:\nConsider these four triplets:\n\n(a[0], b[1], c[0]): 1 XOR 3 XOR 1 = 0112\n(a[1], b[1], c[0]): 1 XOR 3 XOR 1 = 0112\n(a[0], b[0], c[1]): 1 XOR 2 XOR 5 = 1102\n(a[1], b[0], c[1]): 1 XOR 2 XOR 5 = 1102\n\n\n \nConstraints:\n\n1 <= a.length, b.length, c.length <= 105\n0 <= a[i], b[i], c[i] <= 109\n\n", "starter_code": "class Solution:\n    def tripletCount(self, a: List[int], b: List[int], c: List[int]) -> int:\n        ", "completion": "class Solution:\n    def tripletCount(self, a: List[int], b: List[int], c: List[int]) -> int:\n        cnt1 = Counter(x.bit_count() & 1 for x in a)\n        cnt2 = Counter(x.bit_count() & 1 for x in b)\n        cnt3 = Counter(x.bit_count() & 1 for x in c)\n        ans = 0\n        for i in range(2):\n            for j in range(2):\n                for k in range(2):\n                    if (i + j + k) & 1 ^ 1:\n                        ans += cnt1[i] * cnt2[j] * cnt3[k]\n        return ans\n", "entry_point": "Solution().tripletCount", "test": "def check(candidate):\n    assert candidate(a = [10, 20, 30],b = [15, 25, 35],c = [5, 10, 15]) == 9\n    assert candidate(a = [1, 3, 5],b = [2, 4, 6],c = [7, 8, 9]) == 14\n    assert candidate(a = [1000000000],b = [1000000000],c = [1000000000]) == 0\n    assert candidate(a = [2, 4, 6],b = [1, 3, 5],c = [0, 2, 4]) == 14\n    assert candidate(a = [0, 0, 0],b = [0, 0, 0],c = [0, 0, 0]) == 27\n    assert candidate(a = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5],b = [6, 7, 8, 9, 10],c = [11, 12, 13, 14, 15]) == 63\n    assert candidate(a = [0, 1, 2],b = [3, 4, 5],c = [6, 7, 8]) == 14\n    assert candidate(a = [1],b = [2],c = [3]) == 1\n    assert candidate(a = [10, 11, 12],b = [13, 14, 15],c = [16, 17, 18]) == 13\n    assert candidate(a = [1, 1],b = [2, 3],c = [1, 5]) == 4\n    assert candidate(a = [1000000000, 999999999, 999999998],b = [1000000001, 1000000002, 1000000003],c = [1000000004, 1000000005, 1000000006]) == 14\n    assert candidate(a = [1023, 511, 255, 127, 63],b = [31, 15, 7, 3, 1],c = [0, 0, 0, 0, 0]) == 60\n    assert candidate(a = [10, 15, 20, 25],b = [30, 35, 40, 45],c = [50, 55, 60, 65]) == 32\n    assert candidate(a = [255, 128, 64, 32, 16],b = [8, 4, 2, 1, 0],c = [256, 512, 1024, 2048, 4096]) == 40\n    assert candidate(a = [255, 511, 1023],b = [2047, 4095, 8191],c = [16383, 32767, 65535]) == 13\n    assert candidate(a = [100, 200, 300, 400, 500],b = [101, 202, 303, 404, 505],c = [106, 207, 308, 409, 510]) == 58\n    assert candidate(a = [13, 17, 19, 23, 29, 31],b = [37, 41, 43, 47, 53, 59],c = [61, 67, 71, 73, 79, 83]) == 108\n    assert candidate(a = [255, 128, 64, 32],b = [16, 8, 4, 2],c = [1, 3, 5, 7]) == 32\n    assert candidate(a = [536870912, 268435456, 134217728, 67108864, 33554432, 16777216, 8388608, 4194304, 2097152, 1048576],b = [524288, 262144, 131072, 65536, 32768, 16384, 8192, 4096, 2048, 1024],c = [512, 256, 128, 64, 32, 16, 8, 4, 2, 1]) == 0\n    assert candidate(a = [999999999, 888888888, 777777777, 666666666, 555555555],b = [444444444, 333333333, 222222222, 111111111, 0],c = [1, 2, 4, 8, 16]) == 25\n    assert candidate(a = [1000000, 2000000, 3000000],b = [4000000, 5000000, 6000000],c = [7000000, 8000000, 9000000]) == 14\n    assert candidate(a = [1000000000, 500000000, 250000000, 125000000, 62500000],b = [999999999, 499999999, 249999999, 124999999, 62499999],c = [1000000001, 500000001, 250000001, 125000001, 62500001]) == 75\n    assert candidate(a = [1, 0, 1, 0, 1],b = [0, 1, 0, 